    </em:targetApplication>
    <em:description>Some clients add X-Forwarded-For to HTTP requests in an attempt to help servers identify the originating IP address of a request.  Some clients, however, can set X-Forwarded-For to any arbitrary value.  Some servers assume X-Forwarded-For is unassailable.  No server should.

With this add-on, you can assign an arbitrary IP address to the X-Forwarded-For field, attempt to perform XSS by including HTML in this field, or even attempt SQL injection.</em:description>
